race.description: Hfm: Tiger, Big D & Jock Handicap (C3)
race.comment: Very even finish. SUMMER'S LEGACY (6) resumed from a long break and loomed up but was run over late in a similar race at Belmont. Much better than that and will strip fitter. In-form jockey stays aboard and give another chance. ASTRO WORLD (11) is a lightly raced mare who missed the frame for the first time last start then went for a long spell. Placed 2/2 when fresh and has trialled nicely. Suited at the trip and will go close on best figures. TOURETTO (3) ran on well fresh and did win only other try at course and distance. Can sit closer and will be winding up late. TALK TO WYN (9) was heavily bet latest and on speed but fair when a safely held third. Low draw and with good speed will give them something to catch again. EXTREME LOVE (8) ran on hard fresh and was a close-up fifth at big odds. Expected to be running on hard again.
